props & state 
----------------
props ==> transfer data from 1 component to another component

props is passed in the form of  attribute

ex:<img src = 'abc'>

state
-------
the data itself maintained by the component
the component will maintain the data with itself

component
----------
a piece of ui 

react js expression ==> {}

angular & vues j ==> {{}}

concepts in reactjs
----------------------
state|props|propsTypes|props-drilling(parent-child,child-parent)|contextApi
conditional rendering ?
control rendering map method

lifecycle methods
--------------------
componentDidMount() ==> rendered on DOM
componentWillUpdate() ==> updation & sync with the server
componentDidWIllUnMount()  ==> removes the com from dom 

these are the predefined methods given by react used in class based components

in functional components
lifecycle method is useEffect() ==will perform side effects in our component

useEffect(()=>{
componentDidMount()
return ()=>{
componentWillUnMount

}
},[componentwillUpdate])

